ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR THE SOLIS PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE:

The Solis programming language, including its design, syntax, type system,
and novel approaches, is the intellectual property of Chris M. Perez.

While this software is licensed under MIT for implementation purposes,
the language design, specifications, and novel concepts introduced by Solis
remain the exclusive intellectual property of Chris M. Perez.

Any derivative programming language must:
1. Clearly distinguish itself from Solis
2. Credit Chris M. Perez for any Solis-inspired concepts
3. Not use the name "Solis" or confusingly similar names

Commercial implementations must obtain written permission from Chris M. Perez.
